  Pure Cypher Pattern

  The solution for dynamic relationship types in pure Cypher:

  # Group relationships by type (pure Cypher requires literal relationship types)
  by_type: dict[str, list[tuple[str, str, dict[str, Any]]]] = {}
  for from_uid, to_uid, rel_type, props in relationships:
      if rel_type not in by_type:
          by_type[rel_type] = []
      by_type[rel_type].append((from_uid, to_uid, props or {}))

  # Execute per relationship type with literal type in query
  for rel_type, rels in by_type.items():
      query = f"""
      UNWIND $rels AS rel
      MATCH (from_node {{uid: rel.from_uid}})
      MATCH (to_node {{uid: rel.to_uid}})
      MERGE (from_node)-[r:{rel_type}]->(to_node)
      SET r += rel.props
      RETURN count(r) as created
      """
